We began the week in chillicothe ohio at breakfast in the crispy cream donut shop talking about jobs .
Although the industrial base is not what it was in the fifty's there are more jobs there now than there were last year .
In indiana we met may flora who has no confidence that the government could make health care less costly .
But she is sure that anyone who comes into her beauty shop leaves looking much better .
Doctor bob einhorn in <unk> illinois said he treasures personal relationships with his patients and hopes health care reform won't change that .
